social_posts.post_text: I always decorate this tree by myself, and I love it. It’s very peaceful. 🎄
One of my favorite holiday treats, and they are sooooo easy….Caramel Pretzel Turtles! There are lots of yummy combos using this same method, but this is my fave. Have you tried them?
V. v. pleased with how this front porch turned out! It’s giving hygge. 🎄❤️
These Crisped Prosciutto & Avocado Crostini are so delicious! One of my fave appetizers to take to holiday parties. 🍞🥑🥓🧀
It’s Lucia Day! We celebrated by eating homemade gingersnaps and Lucia Buns and drinking spiced cider. 🕯️
Went for a sleigh ride!

Peppermint Bark Pretzels! So easy and so yummy. The captions wouldn’t work on the video, so here are the directions:
•Put mini pretzels on a rimmed baking sheet lined with parchment or a nonstick mat. I’d do about 50, otherwise it gets chaotic. Just trust me on that.
•Put a candy cane kiss on each pretzel, and pop them in the oven at 375° for 2-3 minutes. Don’t let those kisses start to brown!
•Pull them out and smoosh a dark chocolate wafer onto each kiss. Let them melt, then let them cool and harden. That’s it! ❤️
A gorgeous sunrise today. I thought about editing it to make it better or brighter or more beautiful, but it didn’t need any edits. 🌄
The recipe of the year from @kingarthurbaking was a hit at breakfast this morning. Many enthusiastic thumbs up! 👍🏻
That picture on the bottom right fell MONTHS ago, and I’m proud of myself for finally spending the 30 seconds it took to rehang it. 😅
I think this is my third year ordering Valentine’s Day flowers from @flowersandthyme, and they’re absolutely stunning every year. 💖
Grocery store flowers really stepping it up! 🤩 Happy Valentine’s Day! 💖
We’ve been harvesting limes and meyer lemons all winter! Yes, in Oregon! I have a highlight with details on how we grow citrus here. Lemons and limes do really well, oranges are a struggle. 🍊🍋
I always love when people post airplane window shots on Instagram, so here’s mine! The sunshine in Palm Springs has already melted my frozen PNW heart. ☀️🌴❤️
Not a bad view!

GIVEAWAY!! 📚I’m signing copies of Farmhouse Weekends today @altsummit! @arvidabookco is here and has signed copies for sale until the conference ends Wednesday. I’m putting a link in my stories and my profile to buy one of the signed copies, and you can get it here at Alt or they’ll ship it to you! AND…we’re teaming up to give a copy away! Follow both @luluthebaker and @arvidabookco, leave a comment on this post telling me what you’d do on a trip to Palm Springs, and we’ll choose a winner on Sunday and ship Farmhouse Weekends to you! US residents only. ❤️🌴☀️📚
Spring! I had to grab some pictures of the cherry trees just in case we get more rain/hail/wind to knock all the blossoms off. The weirdest Spring weather this year. 🌸🌧️🌬️

Happy 2nd birthday to Farmhouse Weekends! My pandemic baby. She’s a beauty and I love her. ❤️ Do you have any favorite Farmhouse Weekends recipes? Tell me in the comments! I can’t choose a favorite, but for today I’ll say it’s the quiche, because we just had it for dinner last night. And it was delicious, of course.😘
A pretty PNW sunset sans filter. 💜💖🧡
We may have finally gotten to Spring in Oregon! Maybe. We’re taking this break in the rain to hang flower baskets on our porch and install the firefly lights I had in my Amazon cart for 3 months.
Stocked up on the bare necessities at @johnsonbrosgarden today. 🌱💖☀️
If you know how to train and prune climbing roses, I’m all ears!

We thinned apples in our orchard a few nights ago and it’s was lovely and peaceful. And then we limped across the finish line of another jam-packed school year. Parents and caregivers, cheers to you! Parenting is A LOT! 😵‍💫😂🥰

I got to speak about my books at a ladies luncheon today, and even though I was a little rusty on the public speaking and couldn’t figure out how to get my slide deck to auto advance, it was a really wonderful afternoon. I’m so grateful that this little book has allowed me to connect with so many lovely people over the past seven years. ❤️

Friends, I’m selling this Boden dress for my sis. Brand new, never worn, tags still on. It was originally $298; she’s asking $150 plus shipping. US size 10, UK size 14. Gorgeous chambray with blue embroidery. DM if you’re interested!
Climbing roses free floating in my yard because I don’t know how to train them so I ignore them
If you scroll back through my feed, you can see that August is when I start posting flowers and only flowers. 💖 First dahlia bouquet of the year.
Summer sunset, no filter—Taylor Swift playlist—chocolate vanilla swirl cones
The dahlias always hit their stride just as summer is ending. Dahlias, tea roses, cherry tomatoes, blackberries, oregano, and mint. 💖
Watch me bake the Cream Cake with Fresh Strawberries from Scandinavian Gatherings! It’s so pretty and tastes like heaven. 🍰
The Autumn Broccoli Salad from Farmhouse Weekends is one of my faves! You can make it all year, but I love it most in the fall when the weather starts to cool off and I crave heartier foods.
It’s fall in the garden! When you don’t know how to prune your climbing roses so you just ignore them, you’re rewarded with pretty spectacular rose hips all over. 💖

A very blustery, autumnal weekend calls for cozy baking! These easy pumpkin muffins from Farmhouse Weekends are so delicious. Not too sweet, not too heavy. Perfect for breakfast on a drizzly November weekend. Have you tried them yet? 🍂🍁🍂

I shared a different picture from this angle in my stories and loved the sun flare so much that I decided to give it an official, permanent spot in the feed. 🌈☀️ We’re enjoying a couple of quiet days before the holiday rush starts. How about you?

Happy December 1st, friends! Here are a couple of things I’ve been thinking about:
•I want to be better at posting to my feed and not just my stories, so here we go!
•I recently updated this recipe for Peppermint Kiss Cookies, and it’s a winner! The link is in my profile and my stories.
•I’m trying to pay attention to my newsletter. As in actually write one. So if you’d like to sign up, I’ll put that link in my stories, too. Once a week at the most!
Going to a holiday party armed with puff pastry Christmas trees and these cranberry bliss bars. It’s going to be a delicious night! 😘

I’m sharing some of my favorite holiday appetizers this week, and up first is this easy salami cheese ball. This recipe comes from my Nana and it’s a winner! Get the easy, 4-ingredient recipe at the link in my profile or check my stories.
I spend about 7 minutes a day decorating this tree. It might just be done by Christmas Eve. 😂🎄🤷‍♀️😘

Posting one last picture of Christmas decorations because A) it’s actually sunny here today and I love when sun pours through these front windows; B) I’m not ready to take Christmas down just yet; and C) New Years is still part of Christmas in my mind! Happy New Year, friends! May 2024 bring you all the things you want. ❤️
It’s sunny today and a little warm and I’m wearing my new gardening overalls that I got for Christmas and I’m pruning the climbing roses. 💪☀️
